ce:section.ce:para:
Under the optimized experimental conditions, various concentrations of BPA were used to investigate the sensitivity of the colorimetric sensor in pH 4.0 HAc-NaAc buffer by using ZnFe2O4 as catalyst and H2O2 as an enzyme substrate. On-device images were acquired on a scanner and the mean grey intensity of each zone can be quantifiable by photoshop software. Results showed that the grey intensity decreased with the concentration of BPA increasing, and the grey intensity was proportional to the concentration value of BPA ranging from 10 to 1000nM (Fig. 7
                        ). The equation of linear regression was I
                        =−0.4802c[BPA]+149.55, with a correlation coefficient of 0.9945, where I was the grey intensity. And, the limit of detection (LOD) was 6.18nM (calculated using 3σs/S criteria, where S was the slope of the linear calibration curve, and σs was the standard deviation of intensity in a blank solution, n=11), which was even lower than that of other previously reported methods (Table 1
                        ). The results demonstrated that the proposed method could be used for the determination of BPA effectively.
